description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an enthusiastic, motivated and caring individual looking for a new challenge working with working age adult’s experiencing mental health crisis? Are you looking to learn new skills and work in a team that is friendly and committed to professional development?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so, come join us! Our multi-disciplinary team is excited to welcome new staff to join our expanding service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer you a friendly, welcoming and supportive work environment and help you to develop your knowledge and skills within the field of Community Mental Health crisis care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;High recommendations have been received for this team:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Real team-working, friendly and feels supported, like a family”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“I’ve had training opportunities to support my professional development’’&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“This is a supportive team, committed to delivering high quality care”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;‘’good line management and I have regular monthly supervision”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for people who are highly motivated, passionate, confident and have the skills and knowledge for this role. You will need to have previous experience of working with adults with mental health illness and be able to demonstrate that you are able to support Service Users and their support networks during times of crisis towards the goal of recovery within the community setting. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is essential that applicants are flexible and able to work shifts and unsociable hours as required. Our team is committed to providing treatment, support and interventions within the community as an alternative to hospital admission therefore applicants will need to be able to drive and have access to a car. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Southern Health Foundation Trust will also offer you the below benefits:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• £1,000 if you recommend a friend to come and work in the trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Relocation package up to £8,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Generous annual leave entitlement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Regular clinical supervision and training opportunities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Free parking on site&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• A range of staff discounts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal discussions please contact Kate Lloyd 01256 376413 or by email katrina.lloyd@southernhealth.nhs.uk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
